I"o<p>Sociologists recognize the fact that in reaction to an important event, it is the extremist responses which <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/public-opinion-formation-is-memeplex-propagation">surface</a> first. This can be seen through a memetic lens as the most aggressive memes of an ecosystem reacting timely to the presence of a new entity. For less extremist memes, it might take a while for responses to be <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memetic-psychotherapy-equips-prefrontal-areas-with-mental-tools-for-managing-limbic-friction">rationalized</a>, the drift diffusion might be slower.</p>
